---
/**
 * About Page
 *
 * Displays Andy Woods' complete professional biography, including current role,
 * background, expertise, and contact information.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Andy Woods"
  description="Head of Product at DualEntry, the first AI-native ERP. Previously scaled CockroachDB from pre-revenue to $100M+ ARR."
>
  {/* Header */}
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h1 class="font-sans text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-black">About Me</h1>

    {/* Profile photo - centered on mobile, floated right on desktop */}
    <img
      src="/profile.jpg"
      alt="Andy Woods"
      class="w-48 h-48 rounded-lg object-cover shadow-lg mb-6 md:float-right md:ml-8 md:mb-4"
    />

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-4">
      I'm Head of Product at <a
        href="https://www.dualentry.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">DualEntry</a
      >, the ERP built from the ground up to solve what legacy systems can't. We're the first
      AI-native ERP built after ChatGPT — designed for how finance teams actually work today, not
      retrofitted for it. I lead our product management, design, and education functions, and I'm
      fired up about what we're building alongside a team backed by <a
        href="https://www.khoslaventures.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">Khosla Ventures</a
      > and <a
        href="https://lsvp.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">Lightspeed</a
      >, who co-led our $90M Series A, with <a
        href="https://www.gv.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">GV (Google Ventures)</a
      >, Contrary, and Vesey Ventures.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Previously, I spent 8.5 incredible years at <a
        href="https://www.cockroachlabs.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">Cockroach Labs</a
      >, where I helped scale CockroachDB from pre-revenue to $100M+ ARR and category leadership. I
      led cross-functional teams of 50+ driving our Application and Database Ecosystem, pioneered
      our evolution into the AI-powered application stack, and owned CockroachDB's integration with
      the broader application ecosystem — observability, disaster recovery, change data capture
      (CDC), streaming, and migration workflows across hybrid and cloud environments. I also led
      pricing and packaging strategy, aligning product value with business outcomes through a
      data-driven, iterative approach to product-market-price fit.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-4">
      I started this site to share insights at the intersection of AI, finance, and infrastructure.
      I explore how AI is transforming the systems businesses run on — and how we can build better
      products with these technologies.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-sans text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Background</h2>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
      I have 15+ years of hands-on product development and people leadership, a Kellogg MBA
      (analytics, finance, marketing), and consulting-grade rigor. I specialize in turning ambiguity
      into scalable, margin-enhancing products that users love and businesses trust.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-sans text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Subject Matter Expertise</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
      <li>
        AI-native product development: LLMs, RAG architectures, vector databases, and production
        deployment
      </li>
      <li>Enterprise B2B user journeys across SaaS, open-core, and enterprise licensing models</li>
      <li>
        Go-to-Market (GTM): product-led growth (PLG/PLS), sales-assisted motions, and field sales
        enablement
      </li>
      <li>
        Finance and ERP workflows: how modern finance teams actually operate, from startups to
        public companies
      </li>
      <li>
        Distributed infrastructure and databases, including CSP integrations (AWS, GCP, Azure)
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-sans text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Technical & Strategic Skills</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
      <li>
        People leadership: hiring, coaching, and performance management across product, design, and
        education
      </li>
      <li>Product strategy: investment planning, ROI analysis, budgeting, and analytics</li>
      <li>End-to-end product development: from discovery and design to docs and delivery</li>
      <li>
        Analytics & Financial Modeling: SQL/Looker fluency, revenue forecasting, NRR/NDR, gross
        margin optimization, LTV:CAC, Rule of 40
      </li>
      <li>
        Pricing & monetization: strategy informed by data science, customer research, and business
        modeling
      </li>
      <li>
        Technical: Python, SQL, LLMs (GPT-5, Claude, Vertex AI), RAG, Vector Databases, Prompt
        Engineering
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-sans text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Let's Connect</h2>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-4">
      Always up to explore the intersection of AI, finance, and infrastructure, or debate the
      perfect burger. Reach out on <a
        href="https://twitter.com/iamandywoods"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">X</a
      > or <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrewscottwoods/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">LinkedIn</a
      >.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
      I advise early-stage companies on AI product strategy, 0-1 and 1-10 product development, and
      B2B software. I speak at conferences about building AI-native products, modern product
      management, and how finance and infrastructure are being rebuilt in the AI era.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-sans text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">About This Site</h2>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-4">
      This website was built using <a
        href="https://claude.com/claude-code"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">Claude Code</a
      > and <a
        href="https://astro.build"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">Astro</a
      >. The entire development process, from architecture decisions to implementation, was
      completed in under 4 hours using AI-native development practices.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
      Blog post hero images are AI-generated using <a
        href="https://stability.ai/stable-diffusion"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-black underline hover:opacity-70">Stable Diffusion</a
      > to create custom artwork that complements each article's theme.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
